                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d996">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_MA1">MA</gloss>
                    Palestine/10–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 14, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3726. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 4104.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d996fn1">Dated October 12, not printed.</note> Dept deeply concerned
                    UK intention contribute only half million pounds Palestine relief. While
                    requirements for continued relief program won’t be known until interim report
                        <gloss target="#t_ESM1">ESM</gloss>, Dept does not foresee any possibility
                    cutting relief costs in half for coming year. Hopes UK will not make unilateral
                    announcement amount its contribution prior <gloss target="#t_ESM1">ESM</gloss>
                    Report and opportunity US–UK consultation concerning financial implications
                    Palestine refugee program.<note n="2" xml:id="d996fn2">This telegram was
                        repeated to Geneva for Mr. Warren. An Embassy officer discussed the message
                        with Mr. Burrows on October 17. The latter made no offer to increase the
                        British contribution but indicated that the British had no plans to announce
                        a contribution prior to the report of the Economic Survey Mission (telegram
                        4160, October 17, 7 p. m., from London, 501.<gloss target="#t_MA1"
                            >MA</gloss> Palestine/10–1749).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
